Download ${project.name}

  There are several ways to download the artifacts of this project.

* Obtaining Binaries

 The preferred way to obtain these artifacts is through dependency management.
 It is available, along with its tests, sources and Javadoc JARs, in the
 {{{https://search.maven.org/#search|ga|1|g%3A%22${project.groupId}%22%20AND%20a%3Aactive-directory-*%20AND%20v%3A%22${project.version}%22%20AND%20p%3A%22jar%22}Maven Central}} repository.

* Building from Source

  If you rather prefer building from source you either have to check out a working
  copy from the project's public {{{./scm.html}repository}},
  or download a {{{https://github.com/michael-o/${project.artifactId}/archive/refs/tags/${project.version}.zip}source ZIP file}} from GitHub.

  After you have obtained the source code, navigate to the source code directory
  and type <<<mvn install>>>. Prior to that, make sure that you have at least Maven
  $requiredMavenVersion and Java $requiredJavaVersion installed.
  After successful execution the artifacts will be installed to your local repository.

